Suppress the native single-mode "Game UI" windows — merchant repair, level up,
spellmaking, enchanting, alchemy, and rest/wait — when the matching element is in DS
mode, so the companion (bottom-screen) UI is the sole surface. Show the native window
when the element is Vanilla.

Unlike dialogue/container/barter (which updateVisible() already re-asserts by member
pointer), these six windows are NOT members of WindowManager — they live only in
mGuiModeStates[mode].mWindows (constructed as local unique_ptrs and moved into the
GuiModeState). So this suppression is generic: switch on getMode(), read the matching
companionDs*() flag, and if set, hide every window in that mode's GuiModeState. Placed
in updateVisible() (run at the tail of pushGuiMode/popGuiMode), so the gate is applied
the moment the mode is entered. Guarded by !mGuiModes.empty() because it runs before
the later empty-stack early-return and getMode() reads mGuiModes.back().

Safety: none of these six windows override WindowBase::onClose() — they commit their
action on explicit buttons (OK / Create / Wait / ...) and only cancel/discard via
exit()/onCancelButtonClicked. WindowBase::setVisible(false) fires the base onClose()
(a no-op) on the visible->hidden transition, so hiding them mid-mode has no side
effect (no time advance, no attribute commit, no reference reset). This mirrors how
the dialogue/container/barter patches rely on guarded/no-op onClose().

Status: all six elements are "pending" on the Kotlin side (GameUiElement.pending =
locked to VANILLA) because no companion overlay exists for them yet, so companionDs*()
always returns false and this block is INERT today. It is wired now so that removing
`pending` (once an overlay lands) activates suppression with no further native change.
Repair suppresses GM_MerchantRepair only; GM_Repair (self-repair with hammers) is left
untouched by design.

This patch is applied after companion-hide-barter-on-hideui.patch (it appends its six
extern "C" decls to the block that patch chain declared before updateVisible()).

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -647,4 +647,10 @@
     extern "C" bool companionDsConversation();
     extern "C" bool companionDsLooting();
     extern "C" bool companionDsBarter();
+    extern "C" bool companionDsRepair();
+    extern "C" bool companionDsLevelUp();
+    extern "C" bool companionDsSpellmaking();
+    extern "C" bool companionDsEnchanting();
+    extern "C" bool companionDsAlchemy();
+    extern "C" bool companionDsRestWait();
 #endif
@@ -694,4 +700,30 @@
         if (mTradeWindow)
             mTradeWindow->setVisible(!companionDsBarter() && containsMode(GM_Barter));

+        // COMPANION: per-element DS suppression for the single-mode "Game UI" windows not
+        // otherwise managed in updateVisible (repair/levelup/spellmaking/enchanting/alchemy/
+        // rest-wait). Each mode owns its window(s) via mGuiModeStates; when the matching element
+        // is in DS mode, hide them all so the companion bottom screen is the sole surface. These
+        // windows commit on explicit buttons (never onClose()), so hiding on the visible->hidden
+        // transition is side-effect-free. All six are pending today (companionDs*() == false), so
+        // this is inert until a companion overlay lands and the element is un-pended.
+        if (!mGuiModes.empty())
+        {
+            bool suppressModeWindows = false;
+            switch (getMode())
+            {
+                case GM_MerchantRepair: suppressModeWindows = companionDsRepair(); break;
+                case GM_Levelup: suppressModeWindows = companionDsLevelUp(); break;
+                case GM_SpellCreation: suppressModeWindows = companionDsSpellmaking(); break;
+                case GM_Enchanting: suppressModeWindows = companionDsEnchanting(); break;
+                case GM_Alchemy: suppressModeWindows = companionDsAlchemy(); break;
+                case GM_Rest: suppressModeWindows = companionDsRestWait(); break;
+                default: break;
+            }
+            if (suppressModeWindows)
+                for (WindowBase* modeWindow : mGuiModeStates[getMode()].mWindows)
+                    if (modeWindow)
+                        modeWindow->setVisible(false);
+        }
+
         bool gameMode = !isGuiMode();
